P/HARCOURT  – As the President of Port Harcourt Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines and Agriculture (PHCCIMA) Sir Mike Elechi, continues in his stride to open new frontiers of opportunities and value for PHCCIMA’s member companies and Rivers state at large, the President paid a courtesy visit to the Bangladeshi High Commissioner, Mr Masudur Rahman in Abuja. During the visit, the President and the High Commissioner had both expressed their willingness to work closely to jointly foster the huge trade and Investment opportunities begging to be tapped in the areas of Textiles, Leather, Agriculture, ICT, Shipping & Marine Resources, Pharmaceuticals Fishing, Power Generation, Ceramics, Seaports and Crude Oil Refineries development to address the perceived trade imbalances between both countries. The Bangladeshi envoy also promised to visit Rivers state to meet with the organised private sector, and also with the Executive Governor of Rivers State, His Excellency, Nyesom Wike following what he described as impressive imprints of governance by the Rivers State governor. Rivers Council Chairman Tasks Immigration On Recruitment Of… We’ve Brought Down Piracy In Gulf Of Guinea – NIMASA DG In the course of the business meeting, the two bodies also agreed to implement the following decisions reached: Exchange MOUs with the High Commission and other Bangladesh Chambers of Commerce, list PHCCIMA member Companies interested in the identified huge business opportunities in Bangladesh, Hold regular Zoom meetings to link PHCCIMA member Companies with their Bangladesh counterparts and Promote bilateral cooperation in Shipping and Agricultural sectors between both countries. Others are agreement to collaborate with PHCCIMA in all Trade and Investment activities including International Trade Fairs and Exhibitions, to promote rural farming and development in Rivers State, the High Commissioner agreed to pay a facility visit to the chamber and OPS and pledging to facilitate trade missions for PHCCIMA member companies. Mr. Erasmus Chukunda, the Director-General, who accompanied the President to the Bangladeshi High Commission also witnessed the presentation of souvenirs to both organizations.